  "texts": [
    "Following the same procedure as in Section 3.1.2, we extract g-r lags from the simulated light curves using both EzTaoX and JAVELIN; the results are shown in Figure 11.",
    "We find that EzTaoX yields lag measurements comparable to those of JAVELIN even when the transfer function width is as large as 5 days.",
    "Moreover, the n eff -based sample cleaning procedure tends to removes a higher fraction of EzTaoX fits with true lags much smaller than the transfer function width, while preferentially discarding JAVELIN fits with true lags much larger than the width.",
    "This behavior explains the trend noted in Section 3.1.2, where the fraction of discarded JAVELIN fits increases with true lag when the light curves are simulated with a Dirac delta transfer function.",
    "EzTaoX enables reliable and simultaneous characterization of variability and interband lags for the tens of millions of AGNs to be monitored by LSST."
  ],
